    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 7-8 min further or until the onion has softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>ground cinnamon</strong> (not a fan of cinnamon? Only add a little!) and<strong> dried oregano</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p><p>When fragrant, add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until thickened to a ragù-like consistency – this is your <strong>lamb ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortiglioni</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and rinse under <strong>cold water</strong> and set aside for later</p><p>Tip: This will get rid of the starch and will stop the pasta sticking together!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>to a separate pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g] </span><strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked tortiglioni</strong> to the <strong>lamb ragù</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> Greek-style lamb pasta</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>Greek-style lamb pasta</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>and top with the <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese </strong>over the top and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden brown and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Greek-style lamb pastitsio bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad </strong>then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to the bowl and stir it all together – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p><p>Once golden, remove the <strong>Greek-style lamb pastitsio bake</strong> from the oven and allow to cool slightly</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1674.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Greek-style lamb pastitsio bake</strong> with the <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
